      "\n   To do this:\n   - Let `d = gcd(2^{3 * 2ᵏ} - 3, 2^{3 * 2ˡ} - 3)`. \n   - Then `d` divides `(2^{3 * 2ˡ} - 3) - (2^{3 * 2ᵏ})^{2^{l - k}} mod d = 3 - 3^{2^{l - k}}`.\n   - So `d` divides `3^{2^{l - k}} - 3`.\n   - Now, try to bound `d`: since `2^{3 * 2ᵏ} - 3 ≡ 0 mod d`, and `2^{3 * 2ᵏ} ≡ 3 mod d`.\n   - If `d` divides `3^{2^{l - k}} - 3`, then `d ≤ 3^{2^{l - k}} - 3`.\n   - This seems messy.\n\n   Alternative simpler approach: Choose exponents carefully to ensure that",
      "\n  use {⟨2 ^ n + 2, by\n      have : 2 ^ n + 2 > 0 := by positivity\n      omega⟩ | n : ℕ}\n  constructor\n  · -- Prove that the set is infinite\n    have h : Set.Infinite (Set.range fun n : ℕ => ⟨2 ^ n + 2, by\n        have : 2 ^ n + 2 > 0 := by positivity\n        omega⟩ : Set ℕ+) := by\n      have h₁ : Function.Injective fun n : ℕ => ⟨2 ^ n + 2, by\n          have : 2 ^ n + 2 > 0 := by positivity\n          omega⟩ := by\n        intro n m hnm\n        simp_all [PNat.mk.injEq]\n        <;>\n        (try omega) <;>\n        (try\n          {\n            have h₂ : 2 ^ n + 2 = 2 ^ m + 2 := by omega\n            have h₃ : 2 ^ n = 2 ^ m := by omega\n            have h₄ : n = m := by\n              apply Nat.pow_right_injective (by norm_num : 1 < 2)\n              linarith\n            exact h₄\n          }) <;>\n        omega\n      exact Set.infinite_range_of_injective h₁\n    simpa using h\n  · -- Prove that the set is pairwise coprime\n    intro m n hmn\n    simp only [Set.mem_setOf_eq, Set.mem_range] at hmn\n    rcases hmn with ⟨⟨k, rfl⟩, ⟨l, rfl⟩⟩\n    have h₁ : 2 ^ (2 ^ l + 2) - 3 = 4 ^ 2 ^ l - 3 := by\n      have h₂ : 2 ^ (2 ^ l + 2) = 4 * 2 ^ (2 ^ l + 1) := by\n        have h₃ : 2 ^ (2 ^ l + 2) = 2 ^ (2 ^ l + 1 + 1) := by ring_nf\n        rw [h₃]\n        have h₄ : 2 ^ (2 ^ l + 1 + 1) = 2 ^ (2 ^ l + 1) * 2 := by\n          simp [pow_add, pow_one]\n          <;> ring\n        rw [h₄]\n        <;> ring_nf\n        <;> simp [pow_add, pow_one]\n        <;> ring_nf\n      have h₃ : 2 ^ (2 ^ l + 2) = 4 * (2 ^ (2 ^ l)) * 2 := by\n        calc\n          2 ^ (2 ^ l + 2) = 4 * 2 ^ (2 ^ l + 1) := by rw [h₂]\n          _ = 4 * (2 ^ (2 ^ l + 1)) := by ring\n          _ = 4 * (2 ^ (2 ^ l) * 2) := by\n            have h₄ : 2 ^ (2 ^ l + 1) = 2 ^ (2 ^ l) * 2 := by\n              simp [pow_add, pow_one]\n              <;> ring\n            rw [h₄]\n            <;> ring\n          _ = 4 * (2 ^ (2 ^ l)) * 2 := by ring\n      have h₄ : 2 ^ (2 ^ l + 2) = 4 * 4 ^ (2 ^ l) :=